pub enum GridTemplate { FitContent(Unit), Inherit, Initial, MinMax(Unit, Unit), None, Plain(Vec<Unit>), Repeat(i32, Unit), SubGrid, Unset,
} In the Plain choice, Vec's length will be the column count of grid, and every Unit is the width of each column, Repeat just make this easier, every child are in the same width.

Like the other UI libraries, webassemblly Elvis arms a Virtual-DOM, too. import { Center, Elvis, GestureDetector, State, Text } from "calling-elvis"; class MyState extends State { state = { count: 0, } create() { console.log("The first step is creating the dom."); } update() { console.log("Then we can update it, just like what you saw."); } render() { return Center( GestureDetector( Text("I'm a Elvis fans."), onTap: () => this.setState({ count: this.count + 1 }); ), ); } drop() { console.log("Don't be crue, if you want to drop me."); }
} I won't tell you that I'm not only a React fan but also a Flutter fan, and you'll never know I'm a Emacs fan.
